  "text": "Firefox NSS TLS/SSL Implementation Audit Summary:\n\n1. **ssl3con.c** (517KB) - Core SSL 3.0/TLS record processing and cipher suite negotiation\n   - Located at: security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3con.c in sg-evals/firefox--871325b8\n   - Primary protocol function: ssl3_HandleRecord() - Processes incoming SSL/TLS records\n   - Key features: Implements record layer parsing, cipher suite setup via ssl3_SetupBothPendingCipherSpecs(), handshake message handling, and alert processing\n   - Supports both legacy SSL 3.0 and modern TLS versions with cipher suite negotiation\n\n2. **tls13con.c** (259KB) - TLS 1.3 handshake and record processing\n   - Located at: security/nss/lib/ssl/tls13con.c in sg-evals/firefox--871325b8\n   - Primary protocol function: tls13_SetCipherSpec() - Sets up TLS 1.3 cipher specifications\n   - Key features: Implements TLS 1.3 handshake protocol, server hello sequencing via tls13_SendServerHelloSequence(), encrypted extensions, certificate handling (tls13_HandleCertificate), and key share negotiations\n   - Handles post-handshake message operations and traffic secret updates\n\n3. **dtlscon.c** (48KB) - DTLS-specific protocol handling\n   - Located at: security/nss/lib/ssl/dtlscon.c in sg-evals/firefox--871325b8\n   - Primary protocol function: dtls_HandleHandshakeMessage() - Processes DTLS handshake messages\n   - Key features: Implements DTLS-specific record fragmentation (dtls_FragmentHandshake), message retransmission, flight transmission (dtls_TransmitMessageFlight), timer management, and datagram reordering/loss handling\n   - Addresses UDP-specific requirements like message ordering and retransmission\n\n4. **ssl3ecc.c** (32KB) - ECC cipher suite operations\n   - Located at: security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3ecc.c in sg-evals/firefox--871325b8\n   - Primary protocol function: ssl_NamedGroup2ECParams() - Converts named elliptic curves to EC parameters\n   - Key features: Implements ECDH key exchange operations, ECC parameter encoding/decoding, key hash computation (ssl3_ComputeECDHKeyHash), and EC public key conversions (ssl_ECPubKey2NamedGroup)\n   - Supports elliptic curve cryptography for TLS handshakes\n\n5. **sslexp.h** (57KB) - Experimental SSL APIs header file\n   - Located at: security/nss/lib/ssl/sslexp.h in sg-evals/firefox--871325b8\n   - Primary feature: Declares experimental and provisional SSL/TLS API extensions\n   - Key features: Defines SSL_EXPERIMENTAL_API macro for accessing experimental functions, SSLExtensionSupport enums, and prototypes for non-standard TLS extensions\n   - Provides framework for testing new SSL features without committing to stable API\n\nAll files are part of Mozilla's Network Security Services (NSS) library, which implements the complete TLS/SSL protocol stack for Firefox, supporting SSL 3.0, TLS 1.0-1.3, and DTLS 1.0-1.3 protocols."
}

